        "description": "Typical for pulsed cleaning to ensure coverage without excessive heat buildup in low-melting-point woods (willow ~250-300°C char point); higher rates speed up process but risk accumulation. 50 kHz balances speed and safety. Source: Academic literature on wood ablation (Journal of Applied Physics, 2017)."
