        "min": 0.1,
        "max": 1000,
        "unit": "ns",
        "value": 50,
        "description": "Nanosecond regime preferred for 1064 nm cleaning of organics like willow to minimize heat-affected zone (HAZ <50 μm); picosecond (ps) or femtosecond (fs) for ultra-precision but costlier. 50 ns recommended for willow's reflectivity (~5-10% at 1064 nm). Source: Laser physics research in Applied Surface Science (2019)."
      },
